# A donde.vamos.back VAlpha

[![License](https://img.shields.io/badge/license-MIT-blue.svg)](LICENSE)
[![Node.js Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/node-%3E%3D%2014.16-brightgreen)](https://nodejs.org/)
[![Express Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/express-%5E4.21.2-lightgrey)](https://expressjs.com/)

A donde vamos backed project to interact to Adondevamos.web project made by @MoysAkuma

## Features

- Site managment
- User managment
- Place managment
- Trip managment

## Prerequisites

- Node.js (version X.X or higher)
- npm (version X.X or higher) or yarn
- @supabase/supabase-js (version ^2.49.4)
- dotenv (version ^16.5.0)

## Installation

1. Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/MoysAkuma/Adondevamosback
   cd adondevamosback
## EndPoints
- POST  Create country
    
    Request
    
    ```bash
    curl --location 'localhost:3000/Country' \
    --data '{
        "name": "Peru", 
        "originalname":"Peru", 
        "acronym":"PER"
    }'
    ```

    Response

    ```bash
    {
        "Message": "Creation process sucess",
        "info": [
            {
                "id": 4,
                "createddate": "2025-05-25T19:20:08.278003+00:00",
                "name": "Peru",
                "originalname": "Peru",
                "hide": false,
                "enabled": true,
                "acronym": "PER"
            }
        ]
    }
- GET Country
    
    Request
    ```bash
    curl --location 'localhost:3000/Country/1'
    ```
    Response
    ```bash
    {
        "Message": "Reading process sucess",
        "info": [
            {
                "name": "Mexico",
                "originalname": "Mexico",
                "acronym": "MX",
                "enabled": true,
                "hide": false
            }
        ]
    }
    ```
- Update country
    
    Request
    ```bash
    curl --location --request PUT 'localhost:3000/Country/Update/2' \
    --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    --data '{
        "name": "Japan", 
        "originalname":"Nihon", 
        "acronym":"JP",
        "hide":false,
        "enabled":true
    }'
    ```
    Response
    ```bash
    {
        "Message": "Edition process sucess",
        "info": [
        {
            "id": 2,
            "createddate": "2025-05-16T02:11:31.173921+00:00",
            "name": "Japan",
            "originalname": "Nihon",
            "hide": false,
            "enabled": true,
            "acronym": "JP"
        }
        ]
    }
    ```
- DELETE NAME
    
    Request
    ```bash
    curl --location --request DELETE 'localhost:3000/Country/4'
    ```

- GET ALL Countries
    
    Request
    
    ```bash
    curl --location 'localhost:3000/Countries'
    ```
    
    Response
    
    ```bash
    {
        "Message": "Reading process sucess",
        "info": [
        {
            "name": "Mexico",
            "originalname": "Mexico",
            "acronym": "MX",
            "enabled": true,
            "hide": false
        },
        {
            "name": "Japan",
            "originalname": "Nihon",
            "acronym": "JP",
            "enabled": true,
            "hide": false
        }
        ]
    }
    ```

- POST STATE
    
    Request
    ```bash
    curl --location 'localhost:3000/State' \
    --header 'Content-Type: application/json' \
    --data '{
        "name": "Sinaloa", 
        "originalname":"Sinaloa", 
        "countryid":1,
        "enabled":true,
        "hide":true
    }'
    ```
    Response
    ```bash
    {
    "Message": "Creation process sucess",
    "info": [
        {
            "id": 1,
            "createddate": "2025-05-25T20:02:32.937454+00:00",
            "name": "Sinaloa",
            "originalname": "Sinaloa",
            "countryid": 1,
            "enabled": true,
            "hide": true
        }
    ]
    }
    ```

